      "date": "2023-10-31 07:48:15.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\nPlease consider the race when two threads are reclaiming the slab, the first thread hasn't yet managed to free anything, the second thread immediately returns from slab reclaim. Is it possible to get ENOMEM during this race window?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "2badead8ca52b76cf34f024a172f10d25583e989",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2023-10-31 14:50:44.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\n> Please consider the race when two threads are reclaiming the slab,\n > the first thread hasn't yet managed to free anything, the second\n > thread immediately returns from slab reclaim. Is it possible to get\n > ENOMEM during this race window?\n\nIt seems possible, but unlikely?  If it became a real issue then we could have the other thread(s) busy-wait on the trylock until the holder had actually freed something.  Not sure it is worthwhile to do that yet.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
